{
  "texts": [
    "π X e. □ 7.3 Disjointness We no longer fix C and X.",
    "Recall that π X e is the GNS representation of the pure state ω X e. Proposition 7.9.",
    "Let X, Y ∈ Irr Z(C) and e, e ′ ∈ E. Then π X e ≃ u.e.",
    "π Y e ′ if and only if X = Y.",
    "Proof: The statement follows from showing that π X e ≃ u.e."
  ]
}